186.7	Brazil_(film)	Brazil (film)	Brazil is a 1985 British science fiction fantasy/black comedy film directed by Terry Gilliam. It was written by Gilliam, Charles McKeown, and Tom Stoppard and stars Jonathan Pryce. The film also features Robert De Niro, Kim Greist, Michael Palin, Katherine Helmond, Bob Hoskins, and Ian Holm. John Scalzi's Rough Guide to Sci-Fi Movies describes the film as a "dystopian satire".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3e/Brazilposter.jpg/215px-Brazilposter.jpg
